.TH AI-PLAYBOOK-VALIDATE 1 "" "ai-playbook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai\-playbook\-validate \- Check a playbook's structure and (optionally) get an AI review
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBai\-playbook\fR validate [<slug>] [\-\-file <path>] [\-\-no\-ai] [\-\-plain] [\-\-quiet]
.SH DESCRIPTION
validate accepts a single playbook source, expressed one of two ways: a bare
positional <slug> (a saved playbook, resolved through the store) or \-\-file
<path> (a raw markdown file, validated as\-is). Exactly one source must be
given; zero or more than one is a usage error. The exit code reflects ONLY
the deterministic structural check; the AI review pass is advisory and never
affects it.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-file\fR \fI<path>\fR
path to a markdown file to validate
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-ai\fR
skip the AI review pass (structural check only)
.TP
\fB\-\-plain\fR
use plain dot progress instead of the spinner (default when not attached to a terminal)
.TP
\fB\-\-quiet\fR
suppress all output; report the result only via the exit code
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
ai\-playbook validate deploy\-staging
.fi
.PP
.nf
ai\-playbook validate \-\-file ./scratch.md \-\-no\-ai
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
\fBai\-playbook\fR(1)
